## Style Rules
- Explain everything from the ground up.
- Use complete sentences.
- Make it educational, not just technical.
- Avoid jargon unless you define it.
- Do not produce a giant technical wall of tables.
- Use tables only when they make the comparison easier.
- Do not jump to tickers before explaining the fiscal regime.
- Be objective and scenario-based.
- Distinguish facts, campaign promises, market expectations, and investor interpretation.
- Focus on tradable implications, not political commentary.
- Keep the memo clear enough for a smart investor or student to understand.